    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Formerly used to refer to what was considered an order of mammals characterized by either the complete lack of teeth, or teeth that are small and few, such as in armadillos and anteaters. It was subsequently realized that Edentata was polyphyletic, meaning it contained animals that were actually members of unrelated families; thus the order is now considered invalid by cladistic standards.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>在過去被認為屬於哺乳類。特徵為完全無齒、齒小或少齒，例如犰狳與食蟻動物。之後證實貧齒目實屬多源系，亦即其所涵蓋的成員分屬於互無關聯的科；因此依照分支系統的標準來說，貧齒目在現今無法被視為一目。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
